page.title: 01COCKENZIE GENERAL
page.content: Sea covers half the area.The twisting coastline is a maze of Craigs-rocks out at sea-shingle, beach sand, and sand dunes on which by weaving branches into the grass and erecting concrete sleepers coastal protection against{EROSION}has started.The gradual land fall from S-N drains water into the Firth of Forth. Under 4% is woodland, mostly deciduous. RESIDENTIAL areas are at the extreme West and East ends. Recent building sites are increasing this side of Port Seton. For{RECREATION}beaches and Longniddry Golf Course are always open In summer it is better when seasonal events are open. Crossing the area are A198, B6371 and the Inter-city East Coast railway from Edinburgh to London Kings Cross..
